  <Docs>
    <summary>Wraps marshal-by-value object references, allowing them to be returned through an indirection.</summary>
    <remarks>The <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Remoting.ObjectHandle" /> class is used to pass an object (in a wrapped state) between multiple application domains without loading the metadata for the wrapped object in each <see cref="T:System.AppDomain" /> through which the <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Remoting.ObjectHandle" /> travels. Thus, the <see cref="T:System.Runtime.Remoting.ObjectHandle" /> class gives the caller control of when the <see cref="T:System.Type" /> of the remote object is loaded into a domain.</remarks>
  </Docs>
